Global Macro Portfolio Manager (EM), New York

Job Reference: RS0467A
Job Title: Global Macro Portfolio Manager (EM), New York
Location: US & Canada
Product: Other
Role: Finance, Trading

Redstone Commodity Search focus on offering 360° search solutions to the global commodities markets. With a competitive coverage of Trading Houses, Producers, Majors, Utilities, Merchants, Hedge Funds, Investment Banks and Brokerages; Redstone Commodity Search can confidently offer you an edge in today’s volatile market.
Redstone Commodity Search are working with a global macro hedge fund in New York seeking a Portfolio Manager.
Key Responsibilities / Tasks
Responsible for managing a discretionary global macro portfolio with a focus on key emerging markets Identifying key macro themes through detailed fundamental analysis and expressing views through short and longer term investment horizons Trading foreign exchange and interest rates. Close monitoring of EM exposure and responsible for tactical risk management Work closely with strategists, economists and analystsRole reports to CIO
Key Qualifications / Experience
10 years’ experience trading FX and rates in emerging markets Verifiable personal buyside track record (must be able to provide monthly PnL returns)Specialist focus on Emerging Markets and fundamental understanding of key regions (Brazil / Asia / CEE / Eastern Europe / Latin America)A focus on liquid EM instruments (FX and rates strategies)Based in New York (Happy to relocate)

If you match the job description and are keen on applying for this role; please send us a copy of your resume/cover letter to commodities@redstonesearch.com or submit your application through the Vacancy Form.

















